PHASE #3

...But before you get started let's monitor your fatigue.
In this experiment we are interested in
how you balance effort and reward
when choosing between different maths problems.
Throughout the experiment you will be
presented with several maths tests.
These tests vary in the effort they require from
1 (low effort) to 6 (high effort).

INTRODUCTION
PHASE #1
In Phase #1 your task is to familiarise yourself with the 6 effort levels.
You will be presented with tests from each effort level. The effort level is indicated by images like this:
Now that you have learnt the effort levels
we introduce reward.
You will be presented with two options that correspond to different tests. Your task is to select one of these tests. One will require more effort but also has a higher reward.
You win credits if you successfully complete the test.
You can exchange your credits for money at the end.
Choosely carefully! If you get the test wrong or answer too slowly you receive 0 credits.
